    <Paragraph FontSize="22">What Is a GroupBox?
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>The default <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 style provides a box with a visible border and a title. A <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 control can contain only one child element; 
however, that child element can be any UIElement, which includes layout elements like StackPanel and Canvas. These layout elements can contain many items, and enable you to add complex content to a <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>The following illustration shows a <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 that contains a TabControl and a Button that are enclosed in a <Run FontWeight="Bold">StackPanel</Run>
.
    </Paragraph>

