    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Creating a GroupBox
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>The following Extensible Application Markup Language (XAML) example creates a simple <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 that contains a TextBox control, a ListBox control, and a <Run FontWeight="Bold">Button</Run>
 inside a <Run FontWeight="Bold">StackPanel</Run>
.
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>XAML </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>
&lt;GroupBox Margin="0,20,0,0" Width="150" Height="200"> 
&lt;GroupBox.Header> My Favorite City 
&lt;/GroupBox.Header> 
&lt;StackPanel> 
&lt;TextBlock Margin="0,10,0,0">Type your name:
&lt;/TextBlock> 
&lt;TextBox Width="100"/> 
&lt;TextBlock Margin="0,5,0,0">Select your favorite city:
&lt;/TextBlock> 
&lt;TextBlock>Select your name
&lt;/TextBlock> 
&lt;ListBox Name="empName"> 
&lt;ListBoxItem IsSelected="true">Paris
&lt;/ListBoxItem> 
&lt;ListBoxItem>Beijing
&lt;/ListBoxItem> 
&lt;ListBoxItem>Buenos Aires
&lt;/ListBoxItem> 
&lt;ListBoxItem>Chicago
&lt;/ListBoxItem> 
&lt;/ListBox> 
&lt;Button Margin="0,20,0,0" Width="50" Click="SubmitCode">Submit
&lt;/Button> 
&lt;/StackPanel> 
&lt;/GroupBox> </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

