    <Paragraph FontSize="22">GroupBox Behavior and Appearance
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>The <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 control inherits all its properties and methods except for its constructor. A key inherited property for <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 is the Header property, which sets the title of the <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
. The default style for a <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 includes a <Run FontWeight="Bold">Header</Run>
, a Content area, and a Border. The <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 Style hides part of the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Border</Run>
 to make room for the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Header</Run>
 to appear.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>A <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 does not accept focus and is excluded from <Run FontWeight="Bold">Tab</Run>
 key navigation. A <Run FontWeight="Bold">GroupBox</Run>
 sets both Focusable and IsTabStop to <Run FontWeight="Bold">false</Run>
.
    </Paragraph>

